    "department": "General \u0026 Administrative",
    "description": "I'm Hayden Gutry https://www.linkedin.com/in/haydengutry/, Vice President, Strategy at Teamworks. Our Strategy team works directly with senior leadership across go-to-market, product, and G\u0026A, and the work is genuinely broad — M\u0026A diligence, pricing and packaging, board reporting, revenue operations, annual planning. We're a small team with real ownership over consequential decisions, and I'm adding a Senior Strategy Manager who can run complex workstreams independently and raise the quality of everything we put in front of leadership.\n\n\nTHE ROLE\n\n - Own cross-functional strategic projects end-to-end, becoming the internal expert on areas like pricing, revenue operations, or product strategy\n\n - Drive GTM strategy, M\u0026A diligence, and annual planning through rigorous analysis and clear, actionable recommendations\n\n - Build business cases and market models to evaluate new opportunities, pricing strategies, and product expansion\n\n - Distill complex data into executive-ready insights for board reporting and senior leadership\n\n - Partner across products, markets, and functional teams, managing multiple workstreams with proactive communication on timelines and deliverables\n\n\nWHAT I'M LOOKING FOR\n\n\nWHAT YOU MUST BRING\n\n - 3+ years in management consulting, investment banking, corporate strategy, or a comparable professional services role\n\n - Proven ability to lead and influence cross-functional teams, build strong relationships, and navigate tough conversations directly\n\n - Strong analytical skills with hands-on experience building market models and translating complex data into executive-ready recommendations\n\n - Advanced proficiency in Excel/Google Sheets and PowerPoint/Google Slides\n\n - Based in or willing to relocate to the Raleigh-Durham area — this role is on-site at our HQ in Durham\n\n - A genuine passion for sports\n\n\nEVEN BETTER IF\n\n - You have an MBA from a top-tier program\n\n - You have experience in B2B SaaS, sports, or revenue operations\n\n\nWHY THIS ROLE\n\nTeamworks is the operating system for sports, and the Strategy team sits at the center of where we go next. The person in this role will have line of sight into every major strategic decision we make, with real ownership over the analysis and recommendations that shape them.\n\n\n\nABOUT TEAMWORKS\n\nWe're the Operating System for Sports™, powering 6,500+ organizations worldwide, from collegiate programs to every major pro league. Founded in 2006, we've evolved from a messaging tool for college football into the leading sports tech platform, with 500+ global teammates building the future of sports tech. Our solutions span Personnel, Coaching, Performance, Operations, and Intelligence - helping teams recruit smarter, train better, stay compliant, and win.\n\nTeamworks is an equal opportunity employer - if you live our core values every day and are honest, hardworking, humble, committed, innovative, and an all-around exceptional person, you'll thrive at Teamworks. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workforce and take affirmative action to not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, ancestry, physical disability, mental disability, medical condition, genetic information, marital status, sex, gender, gender identity, gender expression, age, sexual orientation, veteran or military status, or any other legally protected characteristics. This policy applies to all employment practices within our organization, including but not limited to recruiting, hiring, promotion, termination, compensation, benefits, and training. Teamworks is committed to providing reasonable accommodations for candidates with disabilities who need assistance during the hiring process. To request a reasonable accommodation, please email talent@teamworks.com.\n\n\nTo all recruitment agencies: Teamworks does not accept agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias, Teamworks employees or any other organization location. Teamworks is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.",
